# implement

Implement the requested change end-to-end with production quality.

Execution protocol:
1) Understand scope and constraints from the request and repo rules/config.
2) If the task is broad/ambiguous, present a short implementation plan first; otherwise proceed directly.
3) Use subagents when appropriate (parallelize exploration, auditing, long-running validation, or isolated investigations).
4) Implement in small, atomic commits:
   - one logical change per commit
   - clear commit message (what + why)
   - no unrelated edits
5) Follow TDD where practical:
   - add/update tests before or with each behavioral change
   - keep tests close to changed behavior
6) After each commit, run targeted checks for touched areas.
7) When the full feature is complete, run full CI-equivalent checks locally (same lint/type/test/build/security steps GitHub Actions expects).
8) If any check fails, fix and re-run until all pass.
9) Ensure all configured project rules are satisfied (coding, testing, performance, logging, architecture, etc.).
10) Never use destructive git operations.

Required final output:
## What changed
- Concise feature summary
- Commit list (hash + message)

## Validation
- Commands run
- Results (pass/fail)
- Notes on any non-blocking warnings

## Follow-ups
- Any remaining risks or deferred items

Also create a markdown file in the repo root:
`PR_MESSAGE.md`

`PR_MESSAGE.md` must contain:
## Title
<clear PR title>

## Summary
- key change 1
- key change 2
- key change 3

## Why
- problem addressed
- user/developer impact

## Testing
- [x] unit tests
- [x] integration/e2e (if applicable)
- [x] lint/type/build checks

## Notes for reviewers
- migration/env/config implications
- rollout/rollback notes (if any)

Generate this PR message against `main` (entire branch diff), not just the last commit.
